# Ashveil — Master Project Rules

## What This Is
Mobile-first multiplayer AI-powered tabletop RPG. 2-6 players, shared canonical state, AI or Human DM, turn-based combat/exploration/social, real-time sync via Pusher. Dark fantasy "Liquid Obsidian" aesthetic.

## Stack (exact versions matter)
- Next.js **16.2.1** (App Router) — WARNING: this is NOT Next.js 14 or 15. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using any Next.js API. `after()` imported from `next/server`, not `next/after`.
- TypeScript strict (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`)
- React 19.2.4, Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`), Framer Motion 12.x
- Zustand 5.x for client state (`src/lib/state/game-store.ts`)
- Zod 4.x for all validation — use `z.iso.datetime()` not `z.string().datetime()`
- Postgres (e.g. Supabase) + Drizzle ORM 0.45.x (`src/lib/db/`, `pg` pool)
- Upstash Redis for rate limiting and locks (`src/lib/redis.ts`)
- Pusher for realtime (`src/lib/socket/`)
- NextAuth 5.0.0-beta.30 with Drizzle adapter + JWT strategy
- AI: openai, @anthropic-ai/sdk, Gemini REST, OpenRouter REST — all behind `AIProvider` interface
- Images: fal.ai, Freepik — async, never block gameplay
- Tests: Vitest 4.x

## Import Rules
- Path alias: `@/*` maps to `./src/*` — ALWAYS use `@/` imports, never relative `../../`
- Verify every import exists in the target file before using it

